Helicopter flights conducted in accordance with visual flight rules (VFR) shall carry a sufficient amount of fuel to allow the helicopter:
1. To fly to the heliport of which the flight is planned and thereafter to fly for a period of 20 minutes at best-range speed;
2. Contingency fuel.

